headline: Lockheed Martin delivers 110 F-35 fighter jets in 2024
summary: The delivery total achieves the higher end of the range of 75 to 110 jet deliveries CEO Jim Taiclet gave in an earnings call last summer.  Lockheed lifted its sales target in July after the Pentagon resumed taking F-35 deliveries following a months-long pause on delays on its software upgrade.  Lockheed has been upgrading the jets under the Technology Refresh 3, or TR-3 program, which gives the F-35 better displays and processing power.

headline: AAR Q2 Earnings Surpass Estimates, Sales Increase Year Over Year
summary: AIR's fiscal second-quarter earnings beat the Zacks Consensus Estimate by 8.4%, while the quarterly sales top the consensus estimate by 5.1%.
